		        <tr>
			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerBioLabel">Eric Peterson is the President and co-founder of Vicious Cycle Software, Inc. and its divisions, Monkey Bar Games and Vicious Engine.  The company is best known for developing games such as Robotech: Battlecry and for creating a comprehensive and fully portable middleware solution for current generation consoles, handhelds, and the PC.  Eric started his games industry career at MicroProse in 1996, first as a 3D artist and later as Art Director.  Along with his industry experience, He also brings his academic training as a traditional and digital artist with a Bachelor of Arts degree from the University of Maryland.  He is responsible for business development, legal affairs, marketing, financials, day-to-day operations, and serves as the company liaison to publishers, licensors, contractors and vendors.</span></td>
